    <Instrument_Host>
        <name>Venera 4</name>
        <type>Spacecraft</type>
        <description>

The Venera 4 spacecraft comprised a carrier bus holding a descent
craft/lander to study Venus. The carrier bus was designed to be a
communications relay for the lander and to study interplanetary space during
cruise and in the vicinity of Venus. It carried a magnetometer, energetic
particle detectors, cosmic ray detectors, ion traps, and far UV photometer
that covered hydrogen and atomic oxygen. Venera 4 was the first mission to
transmit data from the atmosphere of another planet. 

        </description>
